,Recommended,631980,33993459,Posted: 3 August,all,bladechild,"7/10 [Just above neutral grade]Around the five hour mark I was loving this game, and thought this might be the next special thing in the world of ""soulsy"" kind of games. But then not long after it sort of ends with very little fanfare, to which all hope of scope is kind of lost.This is made by a one man dev team so it would be harsh to condemn it for that too much, but the game really needed that added scope that you find in similar games. There aren't enough weapons, and builds are kind of thin due to the stat mechanics. Most weapons function the same outside of some very pointless awakening abilities, do the same kind of DPS regardless of whether you level up STR or AGI. Not much thought was given to items and how they function in the game, and being a ""mage"" is sort of a support thing more than anything.The world is interesting enough, and how you progress through the rooms is very clostrophobic but well done thanks to the decent combat.  But with only 2 or 3 areas needed to progress toward the end, there's very little freedom felt outside of choosing which to tackle first. And because there's very little scope to build your character, the desire to keep exploring kind of wanes.This is a worthwhile 7 hours of your time. But I can't help but want at least 3 times the content you get for a more well rounded experience."
